      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just... it's not even a loud sadness. it's just empty. like, if I disappeared tomorrow, my boss would probably just send a follow-up email about a deadline and that'd be it. my neighbors see me in the hallway maybe once a month and we don't even speak. it feels like the world is just moving on without me, and maybe it's just easier to just... stop trying to keep up. does that make sense? like, if you're already a ghost, does it even matter if you actually leave?",
